President Obama announced his intent to nominate Carolyn Lerner as Special Counsel for the Office of Special Counsel. Lerner is a founding partner of a law firm in Washington, D.C. and has experience in civil rights and employment matters. She has also served as a law clerk and is involved in various non-profit organizations. Lerner holds a B.G.S. from the University of Michigan and a J.D. from New York University School of Law. 

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Timothy Broas as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars. Broas is a partner in a law firm in Washington, D.C. and specializes in criminal defense and securities litigation. He has received several accolades for his work and holds a J.D. from the College of William and Mary and an A.B. in Economics and History from Boston College.